  "body": "The block timer can sometimes trigger as early and in some local tests triggered too early. It might be possible to improve the accuracy of the timer.\n\nImpact of the block timer being triggered too early is that blocks can be created with an invalid block header timestamp leading to the header validation rule to fail and Ibft or Qbft to go to new round.",
